Beef Cheek and Chimi Fries

These beautiful cheeks came from @themeatery 

Today we drink @dosgabachosmezcal 

Beef cheeks can be intimidating to cook but with a lil patience you’ll have the most tender, sticky, gelatinous meat you’ve ever tasted. The first few times I made beef cheeks, I didn’t cook them long enough. Low and slow is the only way. 

Trim and season your beef cheeks. I’m using SPG from @madmoosebbq. Salt and pepper is really all you need. 

Smoke with hickory wood or pellets at 225 until you have a nice bark. This happened for me at about 4 hours in. Next, I braised in a foil pan with W sauce, unfiltered apple cider, knorr beef bullion and pickled jalapeños. This went back on the smoker at 275 until the meat just crumbled in my hands. The finishing temp was 212. I started checking for tenderness at 200 degrees internal. Let it rest for 20 minutes before shredding. 

Fries
Wash and cut your potatoes into fries and place in an ice water bath for an hour. After an hour, drain and dry. Fry in beef tallow for 5 minutes at 325 then remove and increase the temp to 375 and fry for another 2-3 minutes. Remove and season with @mr.franksseasonings Seasoning Salt. 

Grate some provolone over your fries and place under the broiler on high until the cheese is melted. Top with shredded beef cheeks, chimichurri and a little more provolone cheese! Enjoy!!

Teriyaki Sauce 
1/2c Soy sauce
1/2c Brown sugar
1/2c Mirin

Burger

Smash the burgers on your flat top griddle, cast iron pan or inverted grill grates like I’m doing. Add a lil teriyaki to the burgers, flip, more teriyaki and add American cheese. 

Bun Spread
Mayo
@mr.franksseasonings Tropical Sriracha 

Grill up some pineapple. I seasoned mine with Pineapple Teriyaki from @psseasoning and brushed with teriyaki sauce. 

Assemble your burger. Toasted potato bun, spread, butter lettuce, burger, pineapple and teriyaki. Enjoy!

I’ve lost 50lbs since making this video last year. I started my weight loss journey on Jan 3 2020 and this video was 1 month before I hit my heaviest at 205lbs. Today, I’m 155 and feeling much better. 

I’ve learned so much about myself this year and how to live with self control. Self control was something I struggled with so much. I would eat and snack and eat and snack and my health was declining. I was tired and miserable. I needed to make a change so I did and I’m proud of myself for doing it. It wasn’t easy but it also wasn’t hard. 

My point of sharing this is not to convince you to lose weight but to set a goal and stick to it. This applies to anything in life and not just weight loss. Whatever your goal is this coming year, stick to it. You got this! 

Oh and here’s that recipe. 

Prime Rib

2 bone prime rib 
Habanero Avocado oil as a binder
@grandpajs seasoning 

Let the roast come to room temperature before doing anything. Place in oven or smoker at 225 until the internal temp reaches 115. Rest covered for 45 minutes. 

The meat will continue to rise in temp up to 15 degrees. I like my meat medium rare but if you prefer medium, pull the meat at 120 degrees. If you like anything over medium, I’d like to offer you a McDonald’s cheeseburger instead! 🥴

While the meat is resting, heat your oven to 500 degrees. Place the roast in the oven for 10-15 minutes to sear the meat. Rest for 5-10 minutes and slice into it. 

Mushroom Sauce
2 cups sliced baby portobellos
1/2 cup heavy cream
1/4 cup white wine
2tbsp butter
Salt, pepper, garlic 

Sautee mushrooms in butter, add white sun and reduce by 1/3 then add in heavy cream. As it thickens, add in your seasoning.  Pour over your prime rib!

Pulled Pork Nachos! 

Cheese Sauce
1/2 cup half n’ half
1tsp sodium citrate 
- fully dissolve sodium citrate in the half n half over a medium low heat before adding the cheese
1/2lb pepper Jack
2tbsp @blazingstarbbq reaper 
Mix until smooth. The key is low heat 

Cider brined pork 

Brine
1/4 cup salt
1/2 cup brown sugar
3 cups water
Unfiltered apple cider
Rosemary 
Thyme

Mix all brine ingredients and submerge a 3-4lb pork shoulder in it. Cover and place in the fridge overnight. 

Remove the pork from the brine and Pat dry. Save the brine and bring it to a boil. Season with @mrfranksseasonings tropical sriracha and place on smoker at 225 degrees for 4 hours. Baste the pork every hour with the boiled brine. 

At the 4 hour mark, I mixed a coke from the glass bottle with the remaining brine liquid and placed the pork in the liquid uncovered. At 185 internal temp, I covered the pork with foil to braise for the rest of the cook. I pulled the pork off the grill at 203 degrees and let it rest covered for an hour.

I got a request from @strongarmbarandgrill last week for a Spinach and Artichoke Pizza. Let’s get it!! 

Spinach artichoke pizza

Ingredients 
8oz can artichoke hearts chopped 
1 cup mozzarella 
6 cloves garlic chopped
4oz fresh spinach 
2tbsp butter
1.5tbsp flour
1 cup grated Parmesan 
1tsp salt
1tsp pepper
1tsp garlic powder 
1tsp chicken bullion 
2/3 cup milk
1/2 cup heavy cream

White Sauce
Melt the butter in a sauce pan over medium heat and add in garlic. Cook for about 2 minutes then add in flour and whisk until butter and flour is combined. Whisk in milk and heavy cream then add salt, pepper, garlic powder and chicken bullion. Add Parmesan and whisk until the cheese is melted then add in the spinach. Rest and let sauce thicken. 

Place dough in a lightly oiled cast iron, spread sauce on pizza dough, layer your mozzarella on top then spread out the artichokes. Drizzle olive oil around the edges and sprinkle everything bagel seasoning along the outer crust as well as some @biguncsbbqrub pollo diablo. Pre cook the dough on your stove top for 2-3 minutes then place in a 450 degree smoker or oven for 15 minutes. Garnish with chopped parsley and enjoy!

Chicken Alfredo Pizza 🍕 

Pizza Dough: it’s in my book

Chicken Thighs
Fml hot sauce, Ranch seasoning and Bourques Cajun seasoning 
Season and cook until temp is 165 internal
Chop into bite size pieces 

White Sauce
4tbsp butter
4tbsp flour
6 garlic cloves chopped or minced 
1 cup grated Parmesan 
1 cup heavy cream
Black pepper 
Salt 
Basil 
- melt butter and let it brown a bit but don’t burn it. Add in garlic and cook for about 2 minutes then add in flour and whisk until all the flour is dissolved. Add in Parmesan and whisk. Add heavy cream in a lil at a time and whisk. Add basil, pepper and taste as you add salt. The Parmesan cheese adds saltiness so taste as you add in the salt. The sauce will thicken up. 

Spread sauce on your dough, add chicken, add cheese, more chicken, more cheese. If doing this in a cast iron make sure you a lil oil to the pan and cook the crust for about 2 minutes. You’ll see the oil start to bubble in the edges. I like to add everything bagel seasoning to my crust. 

Bake in oven or smoker at 450 for about 15 minutes. Slice and top with fresh Basil. Enjoy!

Cranberry Bacon Jam

Ingredients
1lb bacon cut into small pieces
1.5 cups fresh cranberries
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/4 cup maple syrup
1 jalapeno sliced
1 yellow onion sliced thin
1 shallot sliced thin
1 tbsp minced garlic
Pinch of salt
3 tbsp butter
 
In a pan, crisp up your bacon, remove from pan and keep half of the bacon grease. Add in the butter salt and onions and mix until golden (about 10-15 minutes). Next add in the garlic and jalapeño and cook for 1-2 minutes then add in the brown sugar, maple syrup and the second part of my name, only 2oz’s. Mix and then add in the bacon and cranberries. The cranberries will burst on their own but I decided to smash them to release the juices quicker. Cook until you have a sticky jam. 
 
Grate some Wisconsin Marieke Gouda over some crostinis and place under the broiler to toast and melt the cheese. Top with the cranberry bacon jam, hot honey and fresh basil.

Birria Mac and Cheese

It’s not spaghetti but may I offer you Birria Mac instead? 

Birria recipe is on page 12 of my book!

Birria Oaxaca Cheese Sauce
12oz Oaxaca cheese
1 cup Birria consume
1/2 cup half n half
2 tsp sodium citrate - this makes the cheese silky smooth
Salt to taste

Dissolve sodium citrate in the consume and half in half over medium low heat. Slowly add in cheese and whisk altogether until you have a creamy cheese sauce. Salt as needed. 

Add cheese to cooked macaroni and mix. Top with more Oaxaca cheese and Pork Rind Crumbs or bread crumbs. I used @porkkinggood pork rind crumbs.

Bruschetta Chicken Sandwich 

I love bruschetta and if i see it on a menu, im ordering it. Bruschetta is one of those light and delicious snacks that when you add in some grilled chicken, bread and mozzarella, it becomes the most delicious sandwich. 

Do you love a good bruschetta sandwich? 

Heres how i made the bruchetta mix:

Over medium heat in a cast iron cook up some diced pancetta until crispy then add in 1/2 diced small yellow onion and 5 chopped cloves of garlic. I added in a lil @sciabicas habanero olive oil as well. It adds a touch of heat. 

When the onions start to caramelize add in about 1.5 cups of sliced cherry tomatoes. Taste and add in salt/pepper/red pepper flakes as needed. I added about 1/2tbsp @zarlengo Italian seasoning. 

Transfer to a bowl and add in some chopped basil and fresh grated Parmesan cheese. 

Grill some chicken. Toast a baguette. Spread pesto and borsin cheese and well im sure yiu get the rest. Fresh pesto wouldve been bettter but i had a jar of pesto i didnt want to go to waste.

Garlic Bread Italian Beef Sandwiches

The Beef
3-4lb chuck roast 
Salt
Coarse black pepper
King shallot seasoning 
Lemon ranch seasoning 
Beer
Mozzarella cheese
Parmesan cheese
Butter

2 bulbs of garlic

Season the chuck roast with salt, pepper, king shallot and  place on a 225 degree smoker for 3 hours. I used @knottywood pellets and a few pieces of oak wood in my @campchef xxl pro. 

After a few hours of smoke, place the chuck roast in a pressure cooker with beer, Worcestershire sauce, pepperoncinis with the juice and lemon ranch seasoning. I did 30 minutes and did a manual release. The meat came out perfectly tender. Shred and strain the juices to dip the sandwiches. 

Cheesy Garlic Bread 
Roast 2 bulbs of garlic by cutting it in half, spraying with Wagyu beef tallow from and salt. Wrap in foil and place in a 400 degree oven for 45 minutes. Let the bulbs cool before squeezing. 

Mix 1 diced shallot, roasted garlic, 2 sticks of butter and a little lemon ranch. Spread on both sides of a split ciabatta loaf, grate Parmesan and mozzarella and bake at 350 until the cheese is melted and bubbling. You can also just use your broiler. 

Top the garlic bread with the beef, dip and enjoy. Eagle rare was fantastic with this one! 

That’s all your calories in one sandwich btw. Cheers!

What if the pizza was the edible? 

I didn’t feel like making any dough so let me show you a hack I learned from a friend. 

For a personal sized pizza, I thawed out 4 frozen Rhoades Dinner Rolls in small cast iron. I drizzled some infused avocado oil and covered with a piece of plastic for a few hours. The rolls tripled in size. 

I drizzled more infused oil and pressed down like I was making focaccia bread, covered with a damp towel and let it rest for about 20 minutes while I prepped my other ingredients. 

*toke break

Build your pizza however you like. I like Rao’s pizza sauce when I want a quick pizza but do you. I precook the pizza on the stovetop for a few minutes until I see the edges bubble up and then it’s into a 450 degree oven for 10-12 minutes. 

I put a lil cheese in the edges and under the crust. It turns out fantastic. 

Lastly, I drizzle some Sour D Hot Honey and embark on my space travels. #castironpizza
